# 📚 Three-Level Documentation

**This is a CURSOR-SPECIFIC rule file.**

**Full documentation:** [docs/standards/rules/three-level-docs.md](../../docs/standards/rules/three-level-docs.md)

## Rule for Cursor

Cursor MUST enforce three-level documentation:

- **ALWAYS** create docs in correct level
- **NEVER** mix documentation levels
- **VALIDATE** doc placement

## Levels

**Level 1 — Template Standards** (`docs/`)
- Golden Rules, ADRs, architecture

**Level 2 — Cross-App Business** (`apps/docs/`)
- Product overview, domain models

**Level 3 — Single-App Domain** (`apps/<app>/docs/`)
- App-specific features, SEO

## AI Agent Instructions

When creating documentation:
1. IDENTIFY scope (template/product/app)
2. CREATE in correct level
3. NEVER duplicate across levels

